## Agent Memory

Shared memory file for both Cursor and Claude Code agents. When you encounter a mistake that could recur, or learn something important about this project, append it to this file under the relevant heading below. Keep entries concise. Remove entries that turn out to be wrong or outdated.

**At the end of every task session, update this file** with any new learnings before your final response. Don't ask — just do it. If nothing was learned, skip silently.

### Project structure
- Eleventy (11ty) personal blog with Nunjucks templates
- Agent instructions live in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (Cursor) and `CLAUDE.md` (Claude Code)
- CLAUDE.md uses `@` imports to pull in cursor rules and docs — avoids duplication
- Docs: `docs/commands.md`, `docs/authoring.md`, `docs/tests.md`, `docs/ideas.md`; exploration write-ups: `docs/color-theme-exploration.md` & `docs/font-stack-exploration.md` each have a **Companion tooling** section; quick links under Maintenance in `docs/commands.md`
- `docs/ideas.md` is the task tracker — has Selected, Future, Maybe Don't, and Done sections
- Reminders use format: `- [ ] **REMINDER (YYYY-MM-DD)**: description`
- Eleventy config is modularized in `eleventy/config/` (filters, plugins, events, etc.) and `eleventy/utils/` (markdown, date, CSS utilities)
- `eleventy/config/transforms.js` is intentionally empty — figure wrapping moved to markdown-it plugin at parse time

### Command relationships
- `deploy` runs: `changelog` → `generate-og-images` → `test markdown` → `test frontmatter` → `build` → `test og-images` → rsync → IndexNow; if changelog changed, deploy then commits and pushes it (skipped with `--dry-run`)
- `import-links` is a manual pre-commit step, not part of deploy — run it before building/committing so links can be reviewed and tested locally
- `test fast` runs 13 tests (`wisdom` validates `src/_data/wisdom-entries.yaml`); `test all` adds `a11y`
- Collected wisdom: `src/_data/wisdom-entries.yaml` (same folder as `links.yaml`; YAML parsed twice—Eleventy global `wisdom-entries` + `wisdom.js` → `wisdom`) + `wisdom-build.js` + `wisdom-entries-path.js`. Pagination needs `wisdom` in `getGlobalData()` — not `eleventyComputed` (runs too late). `_data/*.js` callbacks do not receive sibling `_data` keys. Pages `/wisdom/` and `/wisdom/tags/<tag>/`, RSS `/wisdom-feed.xml`, head link in `head/wisdom-feed.njk`; `markdown` filter renders block markdown from YAML; list UI uses `_includes/components/wisdom_entry.njk` (`footer` + `section`, same article grid as blog index; `article.wisdom-entry` skips the title row)
- `dev` auto-generates OG images on file save via `eleventy.beforeWatch`
- `validate` is shortcut for `test html`

### Workflow preferences
- **Stylelint**: `pnpm run lint:css` or `pnpm run test css`; config `.stylelintrc.json` (extends standard; several rules off for this stylesheet — see `docs/tests.md`). `scripts/test/css.js` uses `runTest`/`outputAndExit` like spell; maps Stylelint warnings to `line`/`column`/`ruleId`/`helpUrl` for `formatVerbose`. Included in `test fast`.
- **Harmony lab (color-gallery)**: Inline `linkDeltas` in `generate-gallery.js` must stay aligned with `buildHarmonySchemes` `pair(...)` offsets — recipe math is duplicated for the browser. `tuningSlidersForRecipe` / `[data-harmony-tuning]` wrappers hide analogous / split / skew unless that recipe uses them.
- **Color themes (2026-03)**: Not pursuing “different theme per weekday” on the live site. Goal is to **generate/explore many** wild candidates (widen beyond straight-laced hand-authored palettes), **refine a shortlist**, then ship **2–4 solid dark/light pairs** with good accessibility (APCA / existing contrast tests). **`pnpm run color-gallery`** writes `scripts/color-explore/output/` (gitignored): **collapsible `<details>` sections**; order **hue reference → Harmony lab (one card: recipe select + A/S/K + hue; `themes.json` still has nine `harmony-*` rows) → B&W combo → wild → terminal**; harmony CLI **`--analogous-spread`**, **`--split-spread`**, **`--harmony-skew`** (clamped; echoed in `themes.json` **`harmonyTuning`**); **`--no-extras`** skips harmony+B&W+wild+terminal; **`--hue-sweep`** restores multi-card step wheel (`--step`). Generator keeps **culori OKLCH objects** in memory; **APCA** uses **`toGamut('rgb')` + `formatHex`** for `apca-w3` only — see `docs/color-theme-exploration.md`. Gallery cards use `<section class="card">` (not `<article>`) so site CSS grid doesn’t break the layout.
- **Font stacks (2026-03)**: **`pnpm run font-gallery`** writes `scripts/font-explore/output/` (gitignored): **one** index-shaped preview at **live** `jonplummer.css` type scale (no mini tokens); colors unchanged (`light-dark()`); two `<select>`s (headings `h1`–`h4` vs rest on `#font-preview-jp`) + **Same stack** checkbox to mirror selections; defaults `DEFAULT_HEADING_STACK_ID` / `DEFAULT_BODY_STACK_ID` / `DEFAULT_SYNC_STACKS` in `generate-font-gallery.js`. Data: `modern-font-stacks.js` — see `docs/font-stack-exploration.md`.
- User commits intentionally — never commit without being asked
- Pre-existing unstaged changes should be left alone (don't include unrelated files)
- User values concise communication and clear tradeoff analysis
- User uses both Cursor and Claude Code — this file is the shared memory for both
- When modifying docs, check for stale cross-references across all doc files

### DRY decisions
- **Wisdom data (2026-03)**: `src/_data/wisdom-entries.yaml` + `wisdom.js` + `wisdom-build.js`; duplicate YAML parse accepted for authoring next to `links.yaml`; `test wisdom` asserts build + `getGlobalData().wisdom` vs disk.
- OG image preview uses Eleventy's native `renderFile` shortcode (RenderPlugin) + `og-image-body.njk` partial — no custom Nunjucks env needed
- `generate-og-images.js` has its own Nunjucks env with inline `postDate` — it runs outside Eleventy so needs its own renderer. `extractCssCustomProperties` is now shared from `eleventy/utils/css-utils.js`.
- Shared PDF conversion functions live in `scripts/utils/pdf-utils.js`
- User rejected a `readMarkdownFile()` consolidation utility — the pattern repeats across scripts but a shared helper added indirection without clear payoff

### Gotchas
- `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files have YAML frontmatter (globs, alwaysApply) that Claude Code ignores — content is still valid markdown after the frontmatter
- `convert-pdf-with-notes` exists in package.json but isn't documented in commands.md (intentional or oversight — not yet clarified)
- **Date handling is load-bearing** — `addDateParsing` (timezone-aware) + permalink generation preserve WordPress-era URLs. Do not simplify without verifying every URL remains unchanged.
- Figure captions use the convention: image line immediately followed by `*caption text*` (no blank line). The `markdown-it-figure` plugin in `eleventy/utils/markdown-it-figure.js` handles this at parse time.
- Redirects: add entries to `src/_data/redirects.yaml` — the `src/.htaccess.njk` template renders them automatically via the data cascade. No separate script needed.
- **Eleventy image transform wraps `<img>` in `<picture>`** — when a parent element becomes a CSS grid container, `<picture>` is the grid item, not `<img>`. Target `> picture` for grid placement (e.g., `grid-column: 1 / -1`).
- **Spaces in asset filenames** break markdown link parsing (markdown-it doesn't recognize them as URLs) AND the Eleventy dev server's passthrough mode. Use kebab-case for all asset filenames.
- **Dark mode uses `light-dark()`** — colors are defined once in `:root` with `light-dark(lightVal, darkVal)`. Don't add a separate `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block; add new colors using the same pattern.
- **`scripts/test/color-contrast.js` parses `:root` `light-dark()`** — raw hex or `oklch(...)`; **`scripts/utils/apca-dual.js`** computes Lc on **sRGB** and **Display P3** gamut maps (`sRGBtoY` / `displayP3toY`). **Pass/fail** uses sRGB only; warnings for P3 below min while sRGB passes or ΔLc≥4 while sRGB≥min. Gallery **`themes.json`**: **`worstLcSrgb`** / **`worstLcP3`**. Extend parsing if new color syntax appears in `jonplummer.css`.
- **`docs/archive/accessibility-test-limitations.md` is historical** — a11y (`accessibility.js`) disables axe `color-contrast` on purpose; token/APCA checks are `pnpm run test color-contrast` (in `test fast`). Archive “fix axe timing” items largely superseded unless re-enabling axe contrast is desired.
- **Wisdom entry slugs are optional** — `eleventy/utils/wisdom-build.js` derives stable hash-based ids from `body` when `slug` is missing, and `scripts/test/wisdom-yaml.js` only validates `slug` when provided.
- **Wisdom YAML can break when multiline markdown is serialized as plain inline `body:` strings** — keep wisdom `body` content in block scalar style (`|-`/`|`) when rewriting to avoid mapping/indentation parse errors. Block lines must be indented **more** than the `body:` line (e.g. two extra spaces); same indentation as `body:` is invalid YAML.
- **`mergePostsAndLinks` needs `pageNumber === 0` for “page 1” behavior** — only then does it prepend links dated after the newest post. `src/links-feed.njk` must pass `0` (e.g. `mergePostsAndLinks(links, 0)`); otherwise the feed drops newer links and looks frozen at the latest post date.
- **OG image generation** — Recurses `src/**/*.njk` (excludes `_posts`/`_includes`/`_data`/`assets`). Skips `pagination:` templates (one file → many URLs; use shared `ogImage` like `index.png`). `ogImage: auto` must not trigger perpetual regen: `needsRegeneration` ignores `auto` for path comparison. Deploy OG line uses `filesUpdated` for “unchanged”; ℹ️ only when `ogImage` was absent in front matter but the PNG file already existed.

### What worked
- Parallel agents work well for independent code changes (e.g., two unrelated simplifications at once)
- modern-css.com is a good reference for identifying CSS modernization opportunities
